From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Wed, 19 Nov 2025 19:05:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 27/74] FEDORA: 1566938 - Fix TypeError when printing
 ImportError message in hpfax

Also:
  - recommend libsane-hpaio - duplicated scanners are better than no scanner

Signed-off-by: Tomas Korbar <tkorbar@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Zdenek Dohnal <zdohnal@redhat.com>

Link: https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/hplip/blob/5eb8189bae2c83477564d2da80a10b1588c51eb0/f/hplip-hpfax-importerror-print.patch
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 fax/backend/hpfax.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fax/backend/hpfax.py b/fax/backend/hpfax.py
index f77f284..e82c554 100755
--- a/fax/backend/hpfax.py
+++ b/fax/backend/hpfax.py
@@ -89,7 +89,7 @@ try:
     from base import utils
     #from prnt import cups
 except ImportError as e:
-    bug("Error importing HPLIP modules: %s\n" % (pid, e))
+    bug("Error importing HPLIP modules: %s\n" % (e))
     sys.exit(1)
 
 def handle_sigpipe():
